      <body>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e30"
             subtype="h1">1. Na tràthan</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112423352">
            <form>
               <orth>bròs</orth>
            </form>
            <def>form of porridge made with corn. Taken for breakfast.</def>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e43"
             subtype="h1">2. Am biadh a bhidhte gabhail aig gach tràth</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112429040">
            <form>
               <orth>lìte</orth>
            </form>
            <def>taken at supper time. Made with oatmeal or Indian meal.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112528544">
            <form>
               <orth>falaraidh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>word associated with funeral costs and expenses. “A’ dol a dh’iarraidh falaraidh.” Also used for the cheese, biscuits and drink available after a funeral.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112523720">
            <form>
               <orth>easair</orth>
            </form>
            <def>an oatmeal orientated drink likely to be used to quench the thirst.</def>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e74"
             subtype="h1">Biadh aig amanan sonraichte ’sa bhliadhna</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112444088">
            <form>
               <orth>strùthan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>aig Feill Mhicheil.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112535024">
            <form>
               <orth>caora nollag</orth>
               <pron>[sic]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[sic] </def>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e93"
             subtype="h1">3. Dòighean air biadh a dheasachadh</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idola10">
            <form>
               <orth>hearth</orth>
            </form>
            <def>
               <graphic url="GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadhillust1.jpg" width="300px"/>baking placed in hot alcoves (could not remember the word for this).</def>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e107"
             subtype="h1">4. Fuine</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112508816">
            <form>
               <orth>clàr fuinne</orth>
            </form>
            <def>sloped so that the flour would not fall off.<graphic url="GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadhillust2.jpg" width="300px"/>
            </def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112493336">
            <form>
               <orth>aran corc</orth>
            </form>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112506152">
            <form>
               <orth>aran eorna</orth>
            </form>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112506296">
            <form>
               <orth>aran Innsainneach</orth>
            </form>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112500968">
            <form>
               <orth>taois</orth>
            </form>
            <def>dough.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112492904">
            <form>
               <orth>ga thoinneamh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>kneading.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112499744">
            <form>
               <orth>breacag arain</orth>
            </form>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e163"
             subtype="h1">5. Deochan dhe gach seòrsa</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112527680">
            <form>
               <orth>leann nan biastan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>hops which are put in a bottle with sugar and water left to ferment and used to quench the thirst.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112539560">
            <form>
               <orth>blàthach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>excess juice left after making butter.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112523792">
            <form>
               <orth>mùig</orth>
            </form>
            <def>liquid that is left after making cheese.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112513928">
            <form>
               <orth>deisgeann</orth>
            </form>
            <def>rennet.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112466768">
            <form>
               <orth>gruth</orth>
            </form>
            <def>crowdie.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112458056">
            <form>
               <orth>na riuchd fhein</orth>
            </form>
            <def>in its own right.</def>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-d0e221"
             subtype="h1">6. Biadh no deoch a bhidhte deanamh gu sònraichte do luchd euslan</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112439336">
            <form>
               <orth>càmhraich</orth>
            </form>
            <def>oatmeal and gruel steeped in water to be used to alleviate colds. To be found in ‘port a beul’ Ann a Bodaich na ho.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112489088">
            <form>
               <orth>fualaid</orth>
            </form>
            <def>poultice made with bread.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_GlasgowIandMrsRMacDonaldbiadh-idp112046664">
            <form>
               <orth>gob-a’-choillich</orth>
            </form>
            <def>salted butter which is heated and used for the same purpose as a poultice.</def>
         </entry>
